		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Silverman­_David.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;David Silverman joined the 3i US team in 2000 and has ten years of experience in technology related finance.  He focuses on 3i's late stage efforts, with experience investing across all aspects of the Internet, software and semiconductor industries.  David led 3i’s investments in BlueLithium (acq. by Yahoo), Forte Design Systems, Home Decor Products, RGM and Speakeasy (acq. by Best Buy).  He has also been involved with 3i’s investments in Demand Media, Fotolog (acq. by Hi-Media), Omniture (OMTR) and Vonage (VG). <br><br> 

Before joining the 3i team, David spent three years as vice president in technology investment banking at Robertson Stephens. He has extensive transactional experience in equity corporate finance, leveraged buyouts and recapitalizations.  David also worked as a corporate lawyer at the law firms of Ropes & Gray and Sidley & Austin.  Prior to graduate school, he served during the Bush Administration as an aide to the Counsel to the President, acting as a liaison to several Washington research institutes and to the Executive Office during the President's Deregulation Initiative. <br><br>

David earned his JD from Stanford Law School and graduated summa cum laude from Dartmouth College.

</td>
		
		
